# Backend Architecture Rules

## 1. Architectural Style
Backend must follow Clean Architecture with strict separation of concerns.

---

## 2. Layer Responsibilities

### Domain Layer
- Contains core business logic and entities
- Must be framework-agnostic
- Must not depend on any external systems

---

### Application Layer
- Orchestrates domain logic (use cases)
- Defines application workflows
- Depends only on Domain layer

---

### Infrastructure Layer
- Implements external systems (DB, APIs, messaging)
- Implements interfaces defined by Domain/Application
- Must not contain business logic

---

### Presentation Layer
- Handles API/controllers only
- Translates requests into application use cases
- Must remain thin and stateless

---

## 3. Dependency Rule
Dependencies must always point inward:

Presentation → Application → Domain  
Infrastructure → Domain/Application (via interfaces only)

---

## 4. Domain Integrity Rule
Domain layer must remain pure:
- no framework dependencies
- no I/O logic
- no infrastructure access

---

## 5. Dependency Injection Rule
All dependencies must be injected from the composition root.
No direct instantiation of infrastructure inside Domain or Application layers.